Inxmail
This website uses Inxmail to send newsletters. The provider is Inxmail GmbH, Wentzingerstr. 17, 79106 Freiburg, Germany. Inxmail is a service with which, among other things, the dispatch of newsletters can be organised and analysed. The data you enter for the purpose of subscribing to the newsletter is stored on Inxmail's servers in Germany. If you do not wish Inxmail to analyse your data, you must unsubscribe from the respective newsletter. For this purpose, we provide a corresponding link in every newsletter message.
Data analysis by Inxmail
For analysis purposes, e-mails sent with Inxmail contain a so-called "tracking pixel" that connects to Inxmail's servers when the e-mail is opened. In this way, it can be determined whether a newsletter message has been opened. We can also use Inxmail to determine whether and which links are clicked in the newsletter message. All links in the e-mail are so-called tracking links that can be used to count your clicks. You can find out more about the analysis functions of Inxmail from the following link:
www.inxmail.de/loesungen/e-mail-marketing/reports
Legal basis: Data processing is based on your consent (Art. 6 para. 1 lit. a DSGVO). You can revoke this consent at any time. The legality of the data processing operations that have already taken place remains unaffected by the revocation.
Storage period: The data you have stored with us for the purpose of subscribing to the newsletter will be stored by us until you unsubscribe from the newsletter and deleted both from our servers and from Inxmail's servers after you unsubscribe from the newsletter. This does not affect data stored by us for other purposes (e.g. e-mail addresses for the member area).
Conclusion of a contract for order data processing: We have concluded a contract with Inxmail in which we oblige Inxmail to protect the data of our customers and not to pass it on to third parties.
Geolocation
For geolocation, we use a geodatabase. No data will be sent to an external provider. The geodatabase is located on our server and is updated regularly. The query with the available IP address is carried out exclusively on our server and only the country is determined. There are no other data in our geodatabase. The exact location of the website visitor is not determined. The cookies will be deleted when the browser is closed.
We use geolocation to show you the appropriate calibration service in your country. Geolocation is only required and used for the Torque Service area of our website. Our legitimate interest is to determine which specific requirements exist for torque wrenches calibration in your country.
The data processing is based on our interest resulting from the processing purposes pursuant to Art. 6 para. 1 lit. a) DSGVO.
